{"type":"USJ","version":"3.1","content":[{"type":"book","marker":"id","content":["33-MIC-web.sfm English Arabic Names Version (EANV)"],"code":"MIC"},{"type":"para","marker":"ide","content":["UTF-8\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"h","content":["Micah \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc1","content":["The Book of Micah \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc2","content":["Micah \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc3","content":["Mic \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"mt2","content":["The Book of \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"mt1","content":["Micah \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"1","sid":"MIC 1"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"MIC 1:1"},"The LORD’s",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:1 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["When rendered in ALL CAPITAL LETTERS, “LORD” or “ALLAH” is the translation of Allah’s Proper\nName."]}],"caller":"+"}," word that came to Micah the Morashtite in the days of Jotham, Ahaz, and Hezekiah, kings of Judah, which he saw\nconcerning Samaria and Jerusalem. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"MIC 1:2"},"Hear, you peoples, all of you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Listen, O earth, and all that is therein: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and let the Lord",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:2 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["The word translated “Lord” is\n“Adonai.”"]}],"caller":"+"}," ALLAH be witness against you, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the Lord from his holy temple. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"MIC 1:3"},"For, behold,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:3 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["“Behold”, from “הִנֵּה”, means look at, take notice, observe, see, or gaze at. It is often\nused as an interjection."]}],"caller":"+"}," the LORD comes out of his place, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and will come down and tread on the high places of the earth.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"MIC 1:4"},"The mountains melt under him, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the valleys split apart, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["like wax before the fire, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["like waters that are poured down a steep place. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"MIC 1:5"},"“All this is for the disobedience of Yaqub, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and for the sins of the house of Israel. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["What is the disobedience of Yaqub? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Isn’t it Samaria? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["And what are the high places of Judah? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Aren’t they Jerusalem? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"MIC 1:6"},"Therefore I will make Samaria like a rubble heap of the field,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["like places for planting vineyards; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and I will pour down its stones into the valley, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and I will uncover its foundations. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"MIC 1:7"},"All her idols will be beaten to pieces, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and all her temple gifts will be burnt with fire, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and all her images I will destroy; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for of the hire of a prostitute has she gathered them, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and to the hire of a prostitute shall they return.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"MIC 1:8"},"For this I will lament and wail; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will go stripped and naked; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will howl like the jackals, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and moan like the daughters of owls. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"MIC 1:9"},"For her wounds are incurable; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for it has come even to Judah. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["It reaches to the gate of my people, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["even to Jerusalem. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"MIC 1:10"},"Don’t tell it in Gath. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Don’t weep at all. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["At Beth Ophrah",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:10 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Beth Ophrah means literally “House of\nDust.”"]}],"caller":"+"}," I have rolled myself in the dust. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"MIC 1:11"},"Pass on, inhabitant of Shaphir, in nakedness and shame. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The inhabitant of Zaanan won’t come out. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The wailing of Beth Ezel will take from you his protection. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"MIC 1:12"},"For the inhabitant of Maroth waits anxiously for good, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because evil has come down from the LORD to the gate of Jerusalem.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"MIC 1:13"},"Harness the chariot to the swift steed, inhabitant of Lachish.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["She was the beginning of sin to the daughter of Zion; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["For the transgressions of Israel were found in you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"MIC 1:14"},"Therefore you will give a parting gift to Moresheth Gath. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The houses of Achzib will be a deceitful thing to the kings of Israel.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"MIC 1:15"},"I will yet bring to you, inhabitant of Mareshah. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["He who is the glory of Israel will come to Adullam. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"MIC 1:16"},"Shave your heads, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and cut off your hair for the children of your delight. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Enlarge your baldness like the vulture; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for they have gone into captivity from you! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"2","sid":"MIC 2"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"MIC 2:1"},"Woe to those who devise iniquity \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and work evil on their beds! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["When the morning is light, they practise it, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because it is in the power of their hand. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"MIC 2:2"},"They covet fields, and seize them; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and houses, and take them away: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and they oppress a man and his house, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["even a man and his heritage. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"MIC 2:3"},"Therefore the LORD says: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Behold, I am planning against these people a disaster, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["from which you will not remove your necks, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["neither will you walk haughtily; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for it is an evil time. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"MIC 2:4"},"In that day they will take up a parable against you, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and lament with a doleful lamentation, saying, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["‘We are utterly ruined! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["My people’s possession is divided up. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Indeed he takes it from me and assigns our fields to traitors!’”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"MIC 2:5"},"Therefore you will have no one who divides the land by lot in the LORD’s assembly.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"MIC 2:6"},"“Don’t prophesy!” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They prophesy. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Don’t prophesy about these things. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Disgrace won’t overtake us.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"MIC 2:7"},"Shall it be said, O house of Yaqub: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“Is the LORD’s Spirit angry? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Are these his doings? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Don’t my words do good to him who walks blamelessly?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"MIC 2:8"},"But lately my people have risen up as an enemy. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["You strip the robe and clothing from those who pass by without a care, returning from battle.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"MIC 2:9"},"You drive the women of my people out from their pleasant houses;\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["from their young children you take away my blessing forever.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"MIC 2:10"},"Arise, and depart! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["For this is not your resting place, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because of uncleanness that destroys, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["even with a grievous destruction. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"MIC 2:11"},"If a man walking in a spirit of falsehood lies: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“I will prophesy to you of wine and of strong drink;” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["he would be the prophet of this people. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"MIC 2:12"},"I will surely assemble, Yaqub, all of you; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will surely gather the remnant of Israel; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I will put them together as the sheep of Bozrah, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["as a flock in the middle of their pasture; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they will swarm with people. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"MIC 2:13"},"He who breaks open the way goes up before them. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They break through the gate, and go out. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["And their king passes on before them, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["with the LORD at their head. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"3","sid":"MIC 3"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"MIC 3:1"},"I said, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Please listen, you heads of Yaqub, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and rulers of the house of Israel: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Isn’t it for you to know justice? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"MIC 3:2"},"You who hate the good, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and love the evil; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["who tear off their skin, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and their flesh from off their bones; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"MIC 3:3"},"who also eat the flesh of my people, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and peel their skin from off them, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and break their bones, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and chop them in pieces, as for the pot, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and as meat within the cauldron. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"MIC 3:4"},"Then they will cry to the LORD, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but he will not answer them. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Yes, he will hide his face from them at that time, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because they made their deeds evil.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"MIC 3:5"},"The LORD says concerning the prophets who lead my people astray; for those who feed their teeth, they proclaim, “Peace!”\nand whoever doesn’t provide for their mouths, they prepare war against him:\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"MIC 3:6"},"“Therefore night is over you, with no vision, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and it is dark to you, that you may not divine; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the sun will go down on the prophets, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the day will be black over them. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"MIC 3:7"},"The seers shall be disappointed, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the diviners confounded. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Yes, they shall all cover their lips; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for there is no answer from Allah.”",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["3:7 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["The Hebrew word rendered “Allah” is “אֱלֹהִ֑ים”\n(Elohim)."]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"MIC 3:8"},"But as for me, I am full of power by the LORD’s Spirit, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and of judgement, and of might, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to declare to Yaqub his disobedience, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and to Israel his sin. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"MIC 3:9"},"Please listen to this, you heads of the house of Yaqub, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and rulers of the house of Israel, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["who abhor justice, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and pervert all equity. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"MIC 3:10"},"They build up Zion with blood, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and Jerusalem with iniquity. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"MIC 3:11"},"Her leaders judge for bribes, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and her priests teach for a price, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and her prophets of it tell fortunes for money: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["yet they lean on the LORD, and say, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“Isn’t the LORD amongst us? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["No disaster will come on us.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"MIC 3:12"},"Therefore Zion for your sake will be ploughed like a field,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and Jerusalem will become heaps of rubble, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the mountain of the temple like the high places of a forest.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"4","sid":"MIC 4"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"MIC 4:1"},"But in the latter days, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["it will happen that the mountain of the LORD’s temple will be established on the top of the mountains,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and it will be exalted above the hills; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and peoples will stream to it. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"MIC 4:2"},"Many nations will go and say, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“Come! Let’s go up to the mountain of the LORD, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and to the house of Allah of Yaqub; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and he will teach us of his ways, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and we will walk in his paths.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["For the law will go out of Zion, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the LORD’s word from Jerusalem; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"MIC 4:3"},"and he will judge between many peoples, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and will decide concerning strong nations afar off. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They will beat their swords into ploughshares, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and their spears into pruning hooks. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Nation will not lift up sword against nation, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["neither will they learn war any more. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"MIC 4:4"},"But they will sit every man under his vine and under his fig tree;\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and no one will make them afraid: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["For the mouth of the LORD of Armies has spoken. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"MIC 4:5"},"Indeed all the nations may walk in the name of their gods; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but we will walk in the name of the LORD our Allah forever and ever.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"MIC 4:6"},"“In that day,” says the LORD, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“I will assemble that which is lame, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and I will gather that which is driven away, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and that which I have afflicted; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"MIC 4:7"},"and I will make that which was lame a remnant, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and that which was cast far off a strong nation: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the LORD will reign over them on Mount Zion from then on, even forever.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"MIC 4:8"},"You, tower of the flock, the hill of the daughter of Zion, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to you it will come, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["yes, the former dominion will come, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the kingdom of the daughter of Jerusalem. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"MIC 4:9"},"Now why do you cry out aloud? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Is there no king in you? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Has your counsellor perished, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that pains have taken hold of you as of a woman in travail? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"MIC 4:10"},"Be in pain, and labour to give birth, daughter of Zion, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["like a woman in travail; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for now you will go out of the city, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and will dwell in the field, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and will come even to Babylon. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["There you will be rescued. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["There the LORD will redeem you from the hand of your enemies.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"MIC 4:11"},"Now many nations have assembled against you, that say, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“Let her be defiled, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and let our eye gloat over Zion.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"MIC 4:12"},"But they don’t know the thoughts of the LORD, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["neither do they understand his counsel; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for he has gathered them like the sheaves to the threshing floor.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"MIC 4:13"},"Arise and thresh, daughter of Zion; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for I will make your horn iron, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and I will make your hoofs bronze; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and you will beat in pieces many peoples: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and I will devote their gain to the LORD, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and their substance to the Lord of the whole earth. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"5","sid":"MIC 5"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"MIC 5:1"},"Now you shall gather yourself in troops, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["daughter of troops. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["He has laid siege against us. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They will strike the judge of Israel with a rod on the cheek.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"MIC 5:2"},"But you, Bethlehem Ephrathah, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["being small amongst the clans of Judah, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["out of you one will come out to me that is to be ruler in Israel;\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["whose goings out are from of old, from ancient times. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"MIC 5:3"},"Therefore he will abandon them until the time that she who is in labour gives birth.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Then the rest of his brothers will return to the children of Israel.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"MIC 5:4"},"He shall stand, and shall shepherd in the strength of the LORD,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["in the majesty of the name of the LORD his Allah: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and they will live, for then he will be great to the ends of the earth.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"MIC 5:5"},"He will be our peace when Assyria invades our land, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and when he marches through our fortresses, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["then we will raise against him seven shepherds, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and eight leaders of men. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"MIC 5:6"},"They will rule the land of Assyria with the sword, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the land of Nimrod in its gates. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["He will deliver us from the Assyrian, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["when he invades our land, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and when he marches within our border. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"MIC 5:7"},"The remnant of Yaqub will be amongst many peoples, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["like dew from the LORD, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["like showers on the grass, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that don’t wait for man, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["nor wait for the sons of men. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"MIC 5:8"},"The remnant of Yaqub will be amongst the nations, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["amongst many peoples, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["like a lion amongst the animals of the forest, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["like a young lion amongst the flocks of sheep; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["who, if he goes through, treads down and tears in pieces, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and there is no one to deliver. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"MIC 5:9"},"Let your hand be lifted up above your adversaries, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and let all of your enemies be cut off. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"MIC 5:10"},"“It will happen in that day”, says the LORD, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“that I will cut off your horses out from amongst you, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and will destroy your chariots. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"MIC 5:11"},"I will cut off the cities of your land, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and will tear down all your strongholds. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"MIC 5:12"},"I will destroy witchcraft from your hand; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and you shall have no soothsayers. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"MIC 5:13"},"I will cut off your engraved images and your pillars out from amongst you;\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and you shall no more worship the work of your hands. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"MIC 5:14"},"I will uproot your Asherah poles out from amongst you; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and I will destroy your cities. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"MIC 5:15"},"I will execute vengeance in anger, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and wrath on the nations that didn’t listen.” \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"6","sid":"MIC 6"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"MIC 6:1"},"Listen now to what the LORD says: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Arise, plead your case before the mountains, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and let the hills hear what you have to say. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"MIC 6:2"},"Hear, you mountains, the LORD’s controversy, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and you enduring foundations of the earth; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for the LORD has a controversy with his people, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and he will contend with Israel. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"MIC 6:3"},"My people, what have I done to you? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["How have I burdened you? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Answer me! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"MIC 6:4"},"For I brought you up out of the land of Egypt, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and redeemed you out of the house of bondage. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I sent before you Musa, Harun, and Miriam. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"MIC 6:5"},"My people, remember now what Balak king of Moab devised, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and what Balaam the son of Beor answered him from Shittim to Gilgal,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that you may know the righteous acts of the LORD.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"MIC 6:6"},"How shall I come before the LORD, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and bow myself before the exalted Allah? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Shall I come before him with burnt offerings, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["with calves a year old? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"MIC 6:7"},"Will the LORD be pleased with thousands of rams? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["With tens of thousands of rivers of oil? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Shall I give my firstborn for my disobedience? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The fruit of my body for the sin of my soul? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"MIC 6:8"},"He has shown you, O man, what is good. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["What does the LORD require of you, but to act justly, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to love mercy, and to walk humbly with your Allah? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"MIC 6:9"},"The LORD’s voice calls to the city, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and wisdom sees your name: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Listen to the rod, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and he who appointed it. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"MIC 6:10"},"Are there yet treasures of wickedness in the house of the wicked,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and a short ephah",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["6:10 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["An ephah is a measure of volume (about 22 litres or about 2/3 of a bushel), and a short\nephah is made smaller than a full ephah for the purpose of cheating\ncustomers."]}],"caller":"+"}," that is accursed? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"MIC 6:11"},"Shall I be pure with dishonest scales, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and with a bag of deceitful weights? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"MIC 6:12"},"Her rich men are full of violence, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["her inhabitants speak lies, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and their tongue is deceitful in their speech. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"MIC 6:13"},"Therefore I also have struck you with a grievous wound. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I have made you desolate because of your sins. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"MIC 6:14"},"You shall eat, but not be satisfied. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Your humiliation will be within you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["You will store up, but not save; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and that which you save I will give up to the sword. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"MIC 6:15"},"You will sow, but won’t reap. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["You will tread the olives, but won’t anoint yourself with oil;\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and crush grapes, but won’t drink the wine. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"MIC 6:16"},"For the statutes of Omri are kept, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and all the works of Ahab’s house. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["You walk in their counsels, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that I may make you a ruin, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and her inhabitants a hissing; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["And you will bear the reproach of my people.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"7","sid":"MIC 7"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"MIC 7:1"},"Misery is mine! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Indeed, I am like one who gathers the summer fruits, as gleanings of the vineyard:\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["There is no cluster of grapes to eat. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["My soul desires to eat the early fig. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"MIC 7:2"},"The godly man has perished out of the earth, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and there is no one upright amongst men. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They all lie in wait for blood; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["every man hunts his brother with a net. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"MIC 7:3"},"Their hands are on that which is evil to do it diligently. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The ruler and judge ask for a bribe; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the powerful man dictates the evil desire of his soul. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Thus they conspire together. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"MIC 7:4"},"The best of them is like a brier. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The most upright is worse than a thorn hedge. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["The day of your watchmen, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["even your visitation, has come; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["now is the time of their confusion. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"MIC 7:5"},"Don’t trust in a neighbour. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Don’t put confidence in a friend. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["With the woman lying in your embrace, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["be careful of the words of your mouth! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"MIC 7:6"},"For the son dishonours the father, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the daughter rises up against her mother, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the daughter-in-law against her mother-in-law; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a man’s enemies are the men of his own house. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"MIC 7:7"},"But as for me, I will look to the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will wait for Allah of my salvation. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["My Allah will hear me. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"MIC 7:8"},"Don’t rejoice against me, my enemy. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["When I fall, I will arise. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["When I sit in darkness, the LORD will be a light to me. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"MIC 7:9"},"I will bear the indignation of the LORD, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because I have sinned against him, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["until he pleads my case, and executes judgement for me. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["He will bring me out to the light. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will see his righteousness. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"MIC 7:10"},"Then my enemy will see it, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and shame will cover her who said to me, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["where is Allah your LORD? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Then my enemy will see me and will cover her shame. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Now she will be trodden down like the mire of the streets. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"MIC 7:11"},"A day to build your walls— \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["In that day, he will extend your boundary. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"MIC 7:12"},"In that day they will come to you from Assyria and the cities of Egypt,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and from Egypt even to the River, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and from sea to sea, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and mountain to mountain. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"MIC 7:13"},"Yet the land will be desolate because of those who dwell therein,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for the fruit of their doings. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"MIC 7:14"},"Shepherd your people with your staff, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the flock of your heritage, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["who dwell by themselves in a forest, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["in the middle of fertile pasture land, let them feed; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["in Bashan and Gilead, as in the days of old. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"MIC 7:15"},"“As in the days of your coming out of the land of Egypt, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will show them marvellous things.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"MIC 7:16"},"The nations will see and be ashamed of all their might. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They will lay their hand on their mouth. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Their ears will be deaf. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"MIC 7:17"},"They will lick the dust like a serpent. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Like crawling things of the earth they shall come trembling out of their dens.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They will come with fear to the LORD our Allah, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and will be afraid because of you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"MIC 7:18"},"Who is Allah like you, who pardons iniquity, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and passes over the disobedience of the remnant of his heritage?\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["He doesn’t retain his anger forever, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because he delights in loving kindness. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"MIC 7:19"},"He will again have compassion on us. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["He will tread our iniquities under foot; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and you will cast all their sins into the depths of the sea.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"MIC 7:20"},"You will give truth to Yaqub, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and mercy to Ibrahim, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["as you have sworn to our fathers from the days of old. "]}]}